Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.12,0:00:03.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, all you viewers out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.83,0:00:07.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make \Nsure to keep the room nice and bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.13,0:00:09.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and sit back from the screen, 'kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.33,0:00:19.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You killed Karen, your owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.19,0:00:25.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirits who kill their masters \Ncannot return to the Spirit World.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.82,0:00:28.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will now start to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.72,0:00:30.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of her grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.87,0:00:33.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.22,0:00:58.63,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be all right! I'll yell it out countless times.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.63,0:01:03.70,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe your every tomorrow will be shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.70,0:01:06.05,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,The intersection of all people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.05,0:01:08.66,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,whose dreams have come true is one point:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.66,0:01:13.29,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Never giving up.  And that's why we're not gonna lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.29,0:01:18.47,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,When it seems like you'll be blown away by the headwinds,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.47,0:01:20.62,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,grasp this hand, try to take a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.62,0:01:23.89,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're not alone anymore, got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.01,0:01:29.00,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Go forward, more and more!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.00,0:01:31.52,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up on your awesome dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.52,0:01:32.78,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, don't cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.78,0:01:34.25,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Move on, my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.25,0:01:36.63,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, with the light shining down upon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.63,0:01:38.71,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even think about something like giving up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.71,0:01:41.14,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you trade being hurt again for strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.14,0:01:46.63,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes, always looking straight ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.63,0:01:50.91,Song Subtitles,,0000,0000,0000,,can surely see the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.53,0:02:10.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It all started three years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.23,0:02:15.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I'm heading to the spa now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.41,0:02:17.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You be good boys and run home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.24,0:02:20.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Hey, what about our date today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.68,0:02:18.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.69,0:02:20.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's got another harem?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.76,0:02:21.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.21,0:02:25.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Karen my dear, you're back?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.79,0:02:28.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I must...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.66,0:02:31.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Ram, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.88,0:02:33.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aries!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.59,0:02:38.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Did you call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.73,0:02:40.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.22,0:02:40.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh-boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.65,0:02:42.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's fluffy and cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.97,0:02:42.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.12,0:02:43.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aries!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.08,0:02:46.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do me a favor and keep them company, 'kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:48.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.55,0:02:49.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.90,0:02:51.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.92,0:02:51.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play, fluffy-wuffy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.73,0:02:56.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a spirit for entertaining men, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:02:59.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you disobeying my orders, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.95,0:03:01.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.32,0:03:02.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then it's settled!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:04.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play, Aries!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.45,0:03:04.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go for a drive in my magic wheels!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.36,0:03:09.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Spirit King!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:16.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, when a spirit starts \Ntalking back to her master...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.48,0:03:18.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the world coming to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:22.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Karen, deary... Don't go \Ntreating your spirits so badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.32,0:03:28.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm free to use my property \Nas I see fit, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.34,0:03:31.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Little Aries seems like she's suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.12,0:03:40.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like when you used her as a shield to \Nblock the opposing wizard's attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.81,0:03:44.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:49.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Suffering? Spirits don't \Nhave feelings like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.00,0:03:51.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're just tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.92,0:03:52.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:55.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirits are living things, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.87,0:04:00.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Treat them poorly, and {\i1}you'll {\i0}\Nbe the one suffering next!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.43,0:04:07.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bring your petty grievances to the master!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.74,0:04:11.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I didn't say a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.16,0:04:11.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.22,0:04:16.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Making Master Bob angry at \Nme is no laughing matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.30,0:04:20.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I didn't... I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.98,0:04:23.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Playing innocent, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.39,0:04:24.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:29.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As punishment, I will have you stay \Nin the human world for seven days.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.03,0:04:33.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seven days? But you don't have that \Nsort of magical power, Madame Karen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.45,0:04:34.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.59,0:04:37.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't underestimate me if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.96,0:04:41.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd do better to worry about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.12,0:04:45.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what'll happen to a Spirit that \Nstays in the human world for seven days?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.35,0:04:48.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.80,0:04:50.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.93,0:04:52.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.14,0:04:55.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:57.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use! I'll call you back \Nas many times as it takes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:02.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong. I forcibly \Nswitched places with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.34,0:05:03.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.71,0:05:06.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let it go, Karen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.35,0:05:08.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Leo, the Lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.54,0:05:11.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I was back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:16.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aries and I were both bound \Nby contract to Karen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.94,0:05:20.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you open the gate on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.78,0:05:24.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a spirit designed for \Nbattle and quite tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.61,0:05:28.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can overlook a bit of mistreatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:34.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you continue to do such horrible \Nthings to Aries, I will not forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.66,0:05:38.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what do you, a spirit, plan to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.87,0:05:41.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I should just tell \Nyou straight out today...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.82,0:05:44.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to release Aries \Nand me from our contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:46.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.15,0:05:50.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot bear watching your evil actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.25,0:05:54.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The other spirits fear their keys \Ncoming into your possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.31,0:05:55.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:58.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a disgrace to Celestial Wizards.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:05:59.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.56,0:06:02.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Lion, close!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.60,0:06:10.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Close!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.68,0:06:11.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Close!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:14.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back, Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.08,0:06:20.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't I do a forced closure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.77,0:06:26.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until you release us from your contract, \NI have no intention of going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.47,0:06:30.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,While I am here, you can't \Ncall any other spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.87,0:06:36.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With your magical power, you aren't able to \Ncall more than one spirit at the same time after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.62,0:06:39.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be quite a problem for you, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:42.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if this will go as you plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.55,0:06:45.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your magical power isn't infinite, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:53.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In ten days, my magical power will be used up, \Nand you'll be forced to go back to the Spirit World.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.30,0:06:57.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I used my own magical power to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.37,0:06:59.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your magical power is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.06,0:07:02.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stay here no matter how many days it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.92,0:07:05.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some ruins to the west of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.81,0:07:08.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you reconsider, come see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:16.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare he!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.91,0:07:24.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back, Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.98,0:07:27.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you basically at your limit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:31.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Lion is the leader of the 12 Zodiac Gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.17,0:07:35.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Things that the other spirits \Ncan't handle, I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:39.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until you release us from our contracts, \NI won't leave the human world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.31,0:07:41.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got to be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.69,0:07:45.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You expect me to give up two \Nof the 12 Zodiac gate keys?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.18,0:07:49.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With you, I can earn a whole lot more money!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.86,0:07:51.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.75,0:07:54.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When you feel like releasing us, come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.61,0:07:56.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.70,0:08:02.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.79,0:08:05.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a month already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.17,0:08:09.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do any work with you doing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.75,0:08:13.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I promise... I won't mistreat Aries any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.25,0:08:15.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.77,0:08:17.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.65,0:08:21.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you really regret what \Nyou did, you'd let us free.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.32,0:08:24.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.38,0:08:26.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to hell and die!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.29,0:08:29.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you disappear, I can call Aries again!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.05,0:08:31.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all 'cause you're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:36.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all your fault, damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.32,0:08:43.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting used to being in the Human World.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:52.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't really stop my life-force from \Neroding, but I'm not suffering like before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:56.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been three months...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.33,0:08:59.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should forgive Karen now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:03.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If she mistreats Aries again, \NI can always save her once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.52,0:09:16.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.76,0:09:21.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She took on a job recklessly \Nwithout my permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:26.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She must have been horribly impatient \Nnot being able to work for three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.66,0:09:31.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But Karen shouldn't have been \Nable to call any spirits!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.80,0:09:32.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:37.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A wizard using a large amount\Nof magical power at once
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.00,0:09:41.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,should be able to call forth\Ntwo spirits at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.76,0:09:44.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Karen was betting on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.39,0:09:49.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end her body wasn't able to take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:55.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All I wanted was for Karen \Nto rethink her actions...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.77,0:09:58.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To realize that spirits aren't tools...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.10,0:10:04.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That we have free will, that \Nwe have hearts of our own...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:06.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:08.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.20,0:10:11.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't what I wanted!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.82,0:10:13.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.96,0:10:18.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.52,0:10:25.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the sin I committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.37,0:10:30.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Human life cannot be returned once it is lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.30,0:10:33.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The dead never return, for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.91,0:10:38.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way to repent is \Nfor me to disappear myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:42.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Loke, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:45.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's about time...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.85,0:10:47.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Time? Time for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.92,0:10:50.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Time for me to disappear...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:52.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.14,0:10:55.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Karen...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.47,0:11:06.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since that day, I've been unable \Nto return to the Spirit World.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.20,0:11:07.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Your hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.85,0:11:11.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the law of the Spirit World. The rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.81,0:11:14.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.63,0:11:19.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was never able to forget \Nabout Karen since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.84,0:11:25.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried a lot of things to get my mind \Noff it, but I could never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.45,0:11:30.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've simply been persisting \Nuntil this time came.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.91,0:11:34.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until the moment I disappear \Nin front of Karen's grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.69,0:11:38.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And, at long last, the time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.03,0:11:45.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Lucy, for letting me meet a truly \Nwonderful Celestial Wizard in the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.38,0:11:48.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I'll save you! Don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.51,0:11:51.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Give my regards to everyone at Fairy Tail...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.49,0:11:55.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.32,0:11:56.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.73,0:11:58.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't accept this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.14,0:12:04.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you return to the Spirit World, your \Nlife-force will recover really quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.27,0:12:06.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make it so you can return!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.23,0:12:10.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.48,0:12:13.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The law is the law...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.55,0:12:16.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But... This is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.82,0:12:19.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't actually kill Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.90,0:12:21.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just an unfortunate accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:22.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:25.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Lion, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.27,0:12:27.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Return Loke to the Spirit World!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.42,0:12:30.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Open! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.47,0:12:33.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Open!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.15,0:12:36.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy... That's enough. Please stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.93,0:12:38.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.34,0:12:42.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand by when a friend of \Nmine is disappearing before my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.95,0:12:51.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Lion, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.08,0:12:55.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy! Don't use so much \Nmagical power all at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.06,0:12:58.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I'm going to save you, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.71,0:13:04.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can force open the gate to \Nthe Spirit World... Watch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.17,0:13:06.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.23,0:13:08.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gate of the Lion, I open thee!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.69,0:13:10.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Open!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:12.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't open!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:16.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirits who let their contracted owner \Ndie can't go back to the Spirit World!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.61,0:13:20.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.95,0:13:23.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're starting to erode along with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.33,0:13:26.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate you'll disappear when I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:27.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't die!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.49,0:13:29.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you die...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.42,0:13:34.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of magic to begin with \Nif I can't use it protect my friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.82,0:13:37.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:41.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make my crime any \Nworse than it already is!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.59,0:13:42.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What crime?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:48.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the rule of the Spirit \NWorld, then I'll change it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.98,0:14:10.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.34,0:14:11.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.37,0:14:12.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.24,0:14:14.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Spirit King?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.78,0:14:19.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.07,0:14:23.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The King? You mean the ruler of the Spirits?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.25,0:14:26.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Old friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:36.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is forbidden for we who have compacted with \Nhumans to kill the one who possesses the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.49,0:14:44.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It matters not if it was direct or indirect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.31,0:14:50.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Leo the Lion, you are no longer allowed \Nto return to the Spirit World.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:53.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's going too far!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.11,0:14:55.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't, Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.17,0:14:59.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Old friend... Human girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:03.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That law shall not be changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.69,0:15:09.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, did he show himself because Lucy \Nblurted out that she'd change the rule?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.01,0:15:12.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just for that, the King came himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.42,0:15:15.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For three years... Loke's been \Nsuffering for three years!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.28,0:15:19.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For his friend! For Aries!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.59,0:15:21.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What else could he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.06,0:15:28.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I too am pained by my old friend's wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.73,0:15:30.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.37,0:15:32.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not your "old" friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:35.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's your friend, right now, before your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:38.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me, Mustache Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:41.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mustache?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.41,0:15:42.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.85,0:15:44.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This was an unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:47.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Loke didn't do anything wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.46,0:15:49.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't accept anything but \Nhis complete innocence!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.58,0:15:52.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't accept it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.91,0:15:55.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.84,0:15:58.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want anybody to forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.08,0:16:01.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to repent for my sins!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.82,0:16:05.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:10.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.90,0:16:15.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You disappearing isn't \Ngoing to bring Karen back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.61,0:16:18.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All it will do is create more sadness!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.74,0:16:22.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.65,0:16:26.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Caring about your friends is not a crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.56,0:16:29.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This many spirits... All at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.94,0:16:32.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Karen couldn't do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.87,0:16:41.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you disappear, then Aries, myself, and \Neveryone else here will be filled with sadness!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.38,0:16:46.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be repenting for \Nyour sins at all that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.85,0:16:56.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.89,0:17:05.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All my friends came forward to \Nshow that they feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.38,0:17:06.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.98,0:17:12.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're a spirit too, then you \Nshould know how Loke and Aries felt!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.74,0:17:16.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy, why are you forcing yourself like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.02,0:17:17.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to follow in Karen's footsteps?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.98,0:17:26.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If my old friend goes so far as to say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.30,0:17:31.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it is the law that is in error.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.20,0:17:36.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Leo, who committed the crime \Nfor his brethren Aries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.31,0:17:40.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And you, old friend, who \Ntried to save that Leo...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.63,0:17:47.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Considering the beauty of that bond, I \Nwill make an exception for this incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.16,0:17:54.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Leo, I give thee warrant to \Nreturn to the Spirit World.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.11,0:17:59.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You ain't so bad, Mustache Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.19,0:18:04.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You are pardoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:07.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be grateful to the star's guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.55,0:18:09.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.51,0:18:11.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.44,0:18:23.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you still wish to repent for your sins, \NI order you to aid your friend and live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.95,0:18:29.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe her to be a friend of such worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.93,0:18:33.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You should protect her with your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:44.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.87,0:18:59.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.04,0:19:00.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.11,0:19:05.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.41,0:19:14.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:16.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a spirit, Loke?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.27,0:19:18.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, that's the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.89,0:19:23.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So that weird feeling when we switched \Nplaces that time was from that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.35,0:19:24.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, that's what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.77,0:19:27.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't notice at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.49,0:19:30.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But wait... You're not a \Ncow or a horse or nothin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.81,0:19:34.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You know Virgo, Natsu. She \Nhas a human form, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.15,0:19:36.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but she can turn into a gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.78,0:19:38.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.55,0:19:40.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Loke's the Lion Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.59,0:19:41.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.43,0:19:43.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A grown-up cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:44.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.00,0:19:45.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.31,0:19:47.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.04,0:19:51.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But are you feeling okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.40,0:19:54.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not 100% yet, but I figured \NI'd come to say hi to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.17,0:19:58.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I wanted to see Lucy \Nagain as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.53,0:20:01.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He lllllikes you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.23,0:20:02.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop rolling your tongue!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.80,0:20:06.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's talk, you and I, about the future!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.62,0:20:07.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.82,0:20:08.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I'm jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.68,0:20:10.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I had a spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.58,0:20:11.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.73,0:20:13.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A dragon, duh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.70,0:20:15.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I could test out my \NDragon Slayer magic for real!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.93,0:20:20.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirits aren't things you \Nsummon to test your strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.25,0:20:21.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:23.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spirits are for spinning tales of love...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.73,0:20:24.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You, go back already...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.60,0:20:27.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still not fully recovered, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.16,0:20:28.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.15,0:20:30.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.54,0:20:31.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.66,0:20:33.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tickets for a resort hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.08,0:20:36.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys really helped me out a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.50,0:20:38.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.50,0:20:39.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never stayed at a hotel as fancy as that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.38,0:20:43.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I already gave Erza hers, so please have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.25,0:20:44.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, people!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.33,0:20:45.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you standing around for?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.00,0:20:47.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to leave you behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.60,0:20:49.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that's fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.01,0:20:50.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.58,0:20:52.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll head off just like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.65,0:20:53.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.83,0:20:56.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot, I have to pack for a \Ntrip a little, so hold up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.66,0:20:55.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.87,0:20:59.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like my sins have\Ncompletely disappeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.90,0:21:03.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but you've given me the\Nconfidence now to move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:09.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where once I was a member of Fairy \NTail, now I am your spirit, Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.78,0:21:12.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show up whenever my owner's in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.92,0:21:15.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Think of me as your prince on a white horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.12,0:21:17.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not your owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.44,0:21:19.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your friend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.97,0:21:22.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.70,0:21:25.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, let's count on each other, Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:29.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Same to you, Loke!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.00,0:21:33.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy, we're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.50,0:21:35.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Erza...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.32,0:21:36.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.40,0:21:48.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone here was hurt or lost their life \Nbecause of me, I think I'd suffer a lot like Loke.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.38,0:21:50.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.62,0:21:55.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if we all work together, we can \Novercome any trouble we might have, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.74,0:21:57.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't have said it better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.71,0:21:58.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.08,0:22:01.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let's hurry and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.45,0:22:02.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.55,0:22:05.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's party all day and night, non-stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.22,0:22:09.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a favor from Loke, so we're \Ngoing to have lots of fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.58,0:22:11.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.95,0:22:19.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no way I could have\Nknown that before long,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.88,0:22:24.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza's smile would disappear...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.13,0:23:57.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.59,0:23:59.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to head out for a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.11,0:23:59.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Upa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.99,0:24:02.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're really rarin' to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.20,0:24:03.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.09,0:24:05.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye! I'm going to Heaven on earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.42,0:24:06.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:07.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hit your head or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.85,0:24:09.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll know if you come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.42,0:24:13.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you? You're creepin' me out...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.47,0:24:16.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Tower of Heaven!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.33,0:24:19.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? A fish restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.25,0:24:22.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my paradise!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.60,0:24:24.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy, don't leave me!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.35,0:24:26.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,
